name: Great Snipe
rangeDescription: Breeds northern palearctic region; winters sub-saharan africa
description: Slightly bigger and stockier than Common Snipe, with a long and thick bill, heavily barred belly and contrasting upperwing pattern with dark underwings. Flushes at close range; escape flight is usually slow and short.

name: Apapane
rangeDescription: Kauai, oahu, molokai, maui, and hawaii (hawaiian islands)
description: A blood-red Hawaiian honeycreeper found on all of the larger islands. Smaller and darker red than the Iiwi, with a shorter black bill and white under the tail.

name: Rufous-fronted Prinia
rangeDescription: Thornscrub of india and pakistan (indus river plain)
description: Sandy-colored warbler with a long tail. Note white underparts, pale eyebrow, and rufous-tinged forecrown.

name: Common Loon
rangeDescription: Breeds in northern north america, southern greenland, and iceland; winters from southern alaska and the maritime provinces (canada) to northern mexico, and from iceland and scandinavia to the iberian peninsula
description: A large, heavy-billed loon. Common and widespread in North America; somewhat less common and more local in Europe.

name: Bartlett's Tinamou
rangeDescription: Tropical western amazonian brazil, eastern peru, and northern bolivia
description: Small tinamou of floodplain rainforest. Reddish brown with limited black barring on the wings.
